messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, excuse me, sir, some helicopters came down.
A helicopter came down?
Yes.
Where is this?
In the Indian high school and the Indian middle school.
Is it a crash or a landing?
The middle school, Dayton.
You're saying it's a helicopter crash?
Yes, helicopter crash.
9-1-1, where is your emergency?
Hi, the emergency is in the Medici Field, next to Indian Park Field School.
Indian Field School?
Yes, a helicopter just crashed.
A helicopter just crashed?
Yes, sir.
Do you know if there are any injuries?
I have no idea. I can't see that far. We saw it listing as it went over the house and heard the engine go out and it fell.
Heard the big boom. Have no idea who's in it.
Is anybody hurt?
I don't know. We don't see it. You want me to check it?
Sure. Can you, are you able to safely check?
Hold on. I need to cross here. Oh my God. Somebody's there.
Somebody's hurt?
Yes.
Okay. How bad are they hurt? Can you see?
Oh, and the gasoline has come out.
Okay, don't go near it. Is there any fire?
No, there's no fire here.
Okay, there's no fire. But where are you exactly?
You find Indian Field School?
Yes.
I'm exactly in the front. On the left side of the school.
Okay. How big is the helicopter? Can you see if it's large or small?
Don't move it. Alright, there are two people in the helicopter.
Can anyone safely get them out?
I think he is an instructor.
Can you get him out?
No, I think he can't move. We already have one lady out.
Are you able to get them out of the helicopter?
We don't have to move them.
Alright, but is anyone else with you?
More workers.
Can you talk to the people in the helicopter? Are they conscious?
Hold on.
Okay. Don't move. Stay on the ground.
Stay on the floor. Don't move it. Help is coming.
Are you talking to one of the patients?
Yes.
What's the major complaint? What hurts?
It hurts, don't move.
Alright, try and keep them stable. The ambulance is coming.
Okay, they're taking out the girl.
Sir, how many people are hurt?
Two people on the helicopter.
Is anyone else hurt?
No, everything is okay.
Alright. Officers are there?
Yes, the officers are here.
Thank you very much.
Okay, goodbye.
